Prepare data¶

From the name column of each outlet, seperate the

  • outlet type
  • subcategory
  • line 1, 2,3 of the address, and
  • postcode

Replace month ids with names

In [6]:
def seperate_outlet(text):
    text = re.findall(r'(\[.*?\])', text)
    text = str(text)[1:-1]
    text = text.replace("'", '').replace("[", '').replace("]", '')
    return text
In [7]:
subcat_list = ['Project Space Leeds, Project Space Leeds','no name','Indian Restaurant, Indian Restaurant','convenience_store','Totally Wicked, Totally Wicked','54, 54','restaurant, no name']
   
def update_subcategory(subcategory):
    cat = subcategory
    if cat in subcat_list:
        return None
    elif cat == 'cafe, bar':
        return 'cafe'
    elif cat == 'bar, restaurant':
        return 'bar'
    elif cat == 'cafe, restaurant':
        return 'cafe'
    elif cat == 'Indian Restaurant, Indian Restaurant':
        return 'restaurent'
    else:
        return cat
In [8]:
def find_postcode(text):
    text = re.findall(r'[A-Z]{1,2}[0-9R][0-9A-Z]? [0-9][A-Z]{2}', text)
    text = str(text)[1:-1]
    text = text[:5]
    text = text.replace("'", '')
    text = text.split(' ', 1)[0]
    
    return text
In [9]:
col1 ='outlet'
col2 = 'inv_name'
col3 = 'address'

def prepare_data(dframe):
    dframe[col1] = dframe[col2].apply(seperate_outlet) 
    dframe[['outlet_type','outlet_subcategory']] = dframe[col1].str.split(',\s*', n=1, expand=True)
    dframe[col3] = dframe[col2].str.extract('([^[\]]+)(?:$|\[)', expand=True)
    
    for i in range(4):
         data["address_{}".format(i+1)] = dframe[col3].apply(lambda x: x.split(',')[i] if len(x.split(','))>i else None)
    month = {22018: 'February', 32018: 'March', 42018: 'April', 52018: 'May',62018: 'June', 72018: 'July', 82018: 'August', 92018: 'September'} 
    dframe.visit_month = [month[item] for item in dframe.visit_month]
     
    dframe['outlet_subcategory'] = dframe['outlet_subcategory'].apply(update_subcategory)  
    dframe[col1] = dframe['outlet_type']
    dframe =pd.get_dummies(dframe, columns=['outlet_type'])
    dframe =pd.get_dummies(dframe, columns=['outlet_subcategory'])
    dframe['postcode'] = dframe[col2].apply(find_postcode) 
    dframe = dframe.drop([col2, 'inv_radius','address_4'], axis=1)
    return dframe

month = {'February': 2 ,'March': 3,'April':4, 'May': 5,'June': 6,'July':7, 'August':8,'September':9} 

def order_month(dframe):
    dframe['month_id'] = [month[item] for item in dframe.visit_month]
    dframe.sort_values(by=['month_id'], inplace=True)
    dframe=dframe.drop(['month_id'], axis=1)
    
    return dframe

def remove_punctuation(text):
    '''remove punctuations'''
    import string 
    translator = str.maketrans('', '', string.punctuation)
    return text.translate(translator)

def stopwords(text):
    '''remove stopwords'''
    text = [word.lower() for word in text.split() if word.lower() not in stop_words]
    return " ".join(text)

def apply_all(text):
    """
    This function applies all the functions above into one
    """
    return remove_punctuation(stopwords(text))

















In [280]:



    


data['address_1'] = data['address_1'].apply(apply_all)
